ted": 1767657235, "showcontent": "\u4e00"}, {"id": 2493650, "dou": 0, "doustatus": 0, "douname": "", "username": "\u5927\u540d\u5468\u601d\u8a00", "userid": 1504386, "headpath": "head/2024/6/15/1504386_38563_22_22.png", "updated": 1773478125, "showcontent": "Counting it up, Black has one extra breath, so they need to block one move first. If Black doesn't want to waste their breath, they can only try to pin the piece down, but that won't work because if Black keeps pinning it down, the White pieces below can't take it down by themselves\u2014they only have two breaths left. So White doesn't dare to pin it down and has to remove that piece instead. But removing that piece takes two moves, while Black only used one move to extend their breath. So Black now has one extra breath."}]}
